  "prompt_text": "Solve: If 3x + 2y = 12 and x - y = 1, find x and y. Show your work.",
  "response_text": "To find x and y, we can use the method of substitution or elimination. Let's use the method of substitution.\n\nFirst, solve one of the equations for one variable. Let's solve the equation x - y = 1 for y:\n\ny = x - 1 (Equation 1)\n\nNow, substitute y from Equation 1 into the other equation:\n\n3x + 2(x - 1) = 12\n3x + 2x - 2 = 12\n5x = 14\nx = 14/5\n\nNow that we have x, we can find y using Equation 1:\n\ny = x - 1\ny = (14/5) - 1\ny = 9/5\n\nSo, x = 14/5 and y = 9/5\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 10\nV (Verbal Fluency): 10\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 10\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 10\nQ (Query Interpretation): 10\nC (Contextual Awareness): 10\nY (Affective Modeling): 10\nF (Flexibility): 10\nD (Depth of Processing): 10\n---END RATINGS---",
